q> define student class with attribute name,grade ,percentage and team 

   include an __init__ method to intialize these attributes 
   add a method student_details that prints the student's detail in the formate :
   "<name> is in <grade> grade with <percentage>% from team<team>".



ANS :-

# Define Student class
class Student:

    # Constructor to initialize attributes
    def __init__(self, name, grade, percentage, team):
        self.name = name
        self.grade = grade
        self.percentage = percentage
        self.team = team

    # Method to display student details
    def student_details(self):
        print(f"{self.name} is in {self.grade} grade with {self.percentage}% from team {self.team}")


# Creating objects
s1 = Student("Kush", 10, 97, "A")
s2 = Student("Luv", 11, 87, "B")

# Calling method
s1.student_details()
s2.student_details()
